    <!-- Quality Gates -->
    <div class="feature-detail fade-in" id="quality-gates">
      <div class="feature-detail-body prose">
        <div class="feature-detail-icon" aria-hidden="true">🔒</div>
        <span class="feature-card-tag">Non-negotiable</span>
        <h3>Automated Quality Gates</h3>
        <p>
          Agents don't hand you rough drafts. They fight through quality gates the entire way.
          There is no soft-fail mode.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Lint</strong> — format violations tank the pipeline</li>
          <li><strong>Type check</strong> — strict mode, no <code>any</code> escapes</li>
          <li><strong>Code format</strong> — enforced by CI, not just recommended</li>
          <li><strong>Unit tests</strong> — must pass; no skipping</li>
          <li><strong>Integration tests</strong> — end-to-end verification</li>
          <li><strong>Coverage thresholds</strong> — monotonically increasing, never regress</li>
          <li><strong>CI pipeline</strong> — GitHub Actions gate before merge</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          By the time code reaches you, it has passed every automated check.
          You're the <strong>final gate</strong> — reviewing for intent, architecture, and edge cases.
          Not checking whether the tests pass.
        </p>
